# Report deliverables

After any audit, read-only report, or implementation summary, package it for sharing in **Downloads**.

## Output path

```text
/Users/recharge/Downloads/2MRRW-{ReportType}-{YYYY-MM-DD}.zip
```

Example: `2MRRW-Vercel-Env-Audit-2026-05-22.zip`

## Zip contents

1. Full markdown report (`2MRRW-*-READONLY-*.md`, implementation summary, or audit doc)
2. `README.txt` — one-line description (title or `--desc`)
3. Relevant evidence or snippets (logs, curl output, screenshots) when applicable

**Never** include secrets: `.env`, `.env.local`, credentials files, API keys, or token dumps.

## Helper script

From repo root (when `scripts/zip-report-to-downloads.sh` exists):

```bash
# Single report (+ optional evidence paths)
./scripts/zip-report-to-downloads.sh reports/2MRRW-Vercel-Env-Audit-READONLY-2026-05-22.md

# Override type or description
./scripts/zip-report-to-downloads.sh --type Vercel-Env-Audit path/to/report.md --desc "Vercel production env audit"

# Bundle multiple reports (catch-up / archive)
./scripts/zip-report-to-downloads.sh --archive \
  reports/*.md \
  docs/commerce/*REPORT*.md \
  docs/commerce/*E2E*.md
```

Produces `2MRRW-Reports-Archive-YYYY-MM-DD.zip` for `--archive`.

## Agent checklist

- Finish the markdown report in `reports/` or the relevant `docs/` path first.
- Run the zip script; confirm the printed path under `~/Downloads`.
- For batch catch-up, use `--archive` once rather than many duplicate singles.
